title: Three new members appointed to the Elderly Commission
content_text: The Government today (Thursday) announced the appointment of three new members to the Elderly Commission (EC) to further broaden its representation. They are Mr Peter Wong Hong-yuen, Dr Alfred Chan Cheung-ming and Mr Michael Lai Kam-cheung. Mr Peter Wong Hong-yuen, currently Chairman of the Social Welfare Advisory Committee, had extensive experience in public service. His appointment will provide a useful link between the two committees. Dr Alfred Chan Cheung-ming is an

Associate Professor of the Department of Applied Social Studies at the City University of 
    Hong Kong. He has many years of research work and practical experience in gerontology with 
    numerous publications in the field. Mr Michael Lai Kam-cheung, Chief 
    Executive Officer of St. James' Settlement, has been actively involved in the development 
    of services for the elderly. The appointments will be for a period of 
    one year with effect from July 30, 1999. They will be published in the gazette tomorrow

(Friday).  Welcoming the appointment of the new 
    members, Acting Secretary for Health and Welfare, Mr Gregory Leung, said he looked forward 
    to their contributing to the development of elderly services in Hong Kong. The following is a full membership list 
    of the new EC : Chairman: The Hon Tam Yiu-chung Vice-Chairman : Secretary for Health and Welfare or
